summary.snippet: "😂 Update Dec 2021... pics of Turkey Club and Grilled Ham and Cheese sandwiches!"
"Awesome place for coffee and donuts with a friend or before work in the morning."

most_relevant.description: First off, customer service was great. Polite and offered my friend and I an ice water to cool a 90 degree day. Bought a variety of donuts for my team and received rave reviews. Chewy, soft, fresh, just right. The yeast donuts were delicate and flavorful. The cake donuts had a fresh fried crisp to them. A nice treat for all!

I ordered a turkey club with pastrami added. It was amazing, best sandwich I've had in quite a while. The old man can seem rude, but I think it's just his raspy accent and need to be efficient. When you've got a line out to the parking lot, you gotta move orders. Once business had calmed, he chatted with some customers. As my wife and I were packing up to go, he checked on us and made sure our food was good. He offered boxes and refills too. The atmosphere here was perfect.

I would highly recommend Dimo's, just make sure you know what you want ahead of time 😆 the old man isn't afraid to call you out.

One of my favorite spots in Ann Arbor. The food is amazing. They have a great selection of sandwiches and donuts and the lunch specials are such great deals.

The owner is a wonderfully ingratiating and kind man who will kindly and humbly answer any questions you have about the menu.

Don't forget to ask about the soup.

I heard about this place from a friend. I've been here twice now and it's gotta be one of the best sandwich places I've been to. Large portions and the flavor is on point. Donuts are also equally as good. Just know what you want before you walk up to order

Feb 13th 2024 Paczki day!!! Soo good!!!
Flavors: Blueberry, Raspberry, Strawberry, Apple, Buttercream and Custard 😋

Apple fritters, donuts, and sandwiches are the best in town! Better than Zingerman's Deli in my opinion. Sandwiches are monster sized and great selection to choose from...plus burgers and fries!

Hidden in the menu is a falafel sandwich or platter that's great on a summer day. Love the owner and his humor. Brings a smile and laugh to all who walk through his door. 😂

Update Dec 2021... pics of Turkey Club and Grilled Ham and Cheese sandwiches! Plus order of hash browns with cheddar cheese and veggies! Of course, yummy donuts!

Delicious donuts and great service! I picked up a few dozen donuts for a work event and the cashier was extremely nice and helpful. Everyone at work loved the donuts-- I got a mix of specialty and regular. The regular donuts had a crispy outside and soft inside. I will definitely be returning for more donuts and to try the breakfast sandwitch!

Opens really early which is an advantage if you want early breakfast before work. The food is fresh. The service is quick. The owner welcomed everyone with his hearty humor. The place is spacious and clean. I liked the wooden tables. Mediterranean and Middle Eastern food.

We chose the place due to the fact it was close by. We are not from Ann Arbor. I'm glad we came to Dimo's Deli & Donuts as the food was so good. We will definitely come to eat at Dimo's again when we are in Ann Arbor.
